but I owe you big time.

265
00:22:05,457 --> 00:22:06,625
I owe Ms. Jjang, too.

266
00:22:08,293 --> 00:22:12,597
I wasn't able to be with her
because I couldn't make it up to her.

267
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:17,469
This trial is an opportunity for me.

268
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:21,440
A chance to return to Ms. Jjang.

269
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:26,478
You must have feelings for Ms. Jang.

270
00:22:27,312 --> 00:22:29,481
Yes. A lot.

271
00:22:30,782 --> 00:22:33,018
Get ready. The jury finished deliberating.

272
00:22:44,663 --> 00:22:46,298
IN SESSION

273
00:22:46,465 --> 00:22:52,404
Here is the verdict of case number
2013-1241, Defendant Park Su-ha.

274
00:22:52,471 --> 00:22:54,706
Will the defendant please rise.

275
00:23:05,217 --> 00:23:09,688
Park Su-ha was indicted
for the murder, dismemberment,

276
00:23:09,755 --> 00:23:11,757
and concealment of Min Jun-guk's body.

277
00:23:11,823 --> 00:23:16,294
The defendant argued he did not murder
the victim nor hide the body.

278
00:23:16,361 --> 00:23:18,029
And pleaded not guilty.

279
00:23:18,597 --> 00:23:22,401
The charges were murder,
dismemberment of a body, and concealment.

280
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:25,904
The jury's decision was five to four.

281
00:23:26,204 --> 00:23:27,139
Five to four.

282
00:23:27,205 --> 00:23:32,210
I will take the jury's decision
into consideration to make a ruling.

283
00:23:33,979 --> 00:23:37,883
In a criminal case,
facts should be verified through evidence.

284
00:23:37,949 --> 00:23:44,189
Direct and indirect evidence
can both be used to prove a crime.

285
00:23:45,457 --> 00:23:49,528
Park Su-ha confessed to the crime
during the preliminary investigation.

286
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:52,197
The victim's left hand was found
at the crime scene.

287
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:55,300
And there doesn't seem to be any proof
that the victim is alive.

288
00:23:55,367 --> 00:24:00,472
And the defendant's prints were
on the weapon found at the scene.

289
00:24:00,539 --> 00:24:03,308
There is a strong suspicion

290
00:24:03,375 --> 00:24:07,179
that the defendant could have killed
the victim and concealed the body.

291
00:24:09,047 --> 00:24:14,286
We will take a look
at whether the evidence proves that

292
00:24:14,352 --> 00:24:18,490
the defendant murdered,
mutilated, and concealed the body.

293
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:23,462
First, the defendant's confession was
in line with the charges.

294
00:24:23,528 --> 00:24:27,666
The credibility is doubtful
because the defendant has amnesia.

295
00:24:27,732 --> 00:24:30,969
And it's doubtful
that he could have cut up

296
00:24:31,036 --> 00:24:35,841
the 80kg victim with a knife
that isn't even 20cm long.

297
00:24:35,907 --> 00:24:39,544
And the victim's body
or physical remains were not found.

298
00:24:39,611 --> 00:24:40,645
It's enough to doubt

299
00:24:40,712 --> 00:24:46,551
that there may be other possibilities
other than those presented in the charges.

300
00:24:46,818 --> 00:24:51,523
After the victim took advantage of the law
in a similar case and evaded conviction,

301
00:24:51,590 --> 00:24:53,758
he has continuously sought revenge
through murder,

302
00:24:53,825 --> 00:24:55,627
thus showing
his exceptionally cunning nature.

303
00:24:55,694 --> 00:25:00,365
Also, the victim shared a prison cell
with Hwang Dal-jung.

304
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:02,901
And this case is too similar to his case.

305
00:25:02,968 --> 00:25:07,072
We cannot rule out the possibility
that the victim injured himself and fled.

306
00:25:07,372 --> 00:25:12,944
Thus, we cannot deem the evidence to be
beyond a reasonable doubt.

307
00:25:13,011 --> 00:25:16,548
And in this case, we have no choice
but to rule in favor

308
00:25:16,615 --> 00:25:20,385
of the defendant,
according to the principles.

309
00:25:20,452 --> 00:25:24,823
According to Article 325
of the Penal Code,

310
00:25:25,590 --> 00:25:29,461
the defendant is found not guilty.

311
00:25:45,911 --> 00:25:46,912
Good job.

