Isn't that Park Su-ha?

542
00:47:21,071 --> 00:47:24,408
Yes, it is. Hey, Park Su-ha!

543
00:47:28,545 --> 00:47:31,415
What are you doing here?
Are you looking for someone?

544
00:47:31,748 --> 00:47:34,718
Do you know
where Jang Hye-seong's office is?

545
00:47:35,519 --> 00:47:37,921
Of course we do. She works in our office.

546
00:47:39,957 --> 00:47:42,459
I have to meet her.
Please help me meet her.

547
00:47:45,829 --> 00:47:48,599
-She's not here.
-Ms. Jang, you have a guest.

548
00:47:49,766 --> 00:47:54,738
That's strange.
Her trial starts at three o'clock today.

549
00:47:58,408 --> 00:48:00,577
Tell him I'm not here
and get him out of here.

550
00:48:03,413 --> 00:48:08,385
That's right. She said she would
go home straight from an interview.

551
00:48:09,186 --> 00:48:12,556
What do you mean? She has a trial soon.

552
00:48:12,623 --> 00:48:13,957
The pyramid-scheme one.

553
00:48:14,992 --> 00:48:19,396
It's been postponed.
I don't think you can meet her today.

554
00:48:20,631 --> 00:48:23,100
Okay. I'll come back tomorrow.

555
00:48:25,335 --> 00:48:26,703
Sure. Bye.

556
00:48:30,674 --> 00:48:32,609
He's gone. You can come out.

557
00:48:37,180 --> 00:48:39,549
Shoot. My leg hurts.

558
00:48:40,384 --> 00:48:43,020
What is this? Were you avoiding him?

559
00:48:43,320 --> 00:48:46,023
Did you borrow money from Park Su-ha?

560
00:48:46,089 --> 00:48:49,726
I don't want to get involved
with him now that the trial's over.

561
00:48:50,227 --> 00:48:52,329
Are you going to be okay?

562
00:48:52,396 --> 00:48:55,132
Today's trial is about a pyramid scheme.

563
00:48:55,198 --> 00:48:57,834
That is the worst kind.

564
00:48:58,201 --> 00:49:00,938
There are a lot of victims
who are very aggressive.

565
00:49:01,004 --> 00:49:04,374
How aggressive can they be?
They can't attack the lawyer.

566
00:49:04,441 --> 00:49:07,678
-Give me back my money!
-How much did you take?

567
00:49:07,744 --> 00:49:09,780
-Hey!
-Oh, shit!

568
00:49:10,781 --> 00:49:13,417
How can you defend someone like him?

569
00:49:14,284 --> 00:49:17,020
You'll regret doing this!

570
00:49:17,087 --> 00:49:20,958
How can he send his kid to school abroad
and not pay us back?

571
00:49:21,024 --> 00:49:23,727
Why are you doing this to me?
Let go of my hair!

572
00:49:25,696 --> 00:49:27,097
Stop it!

573
00:49:27,164 --> 00:49:30,567
Do you want to be charged
for violence and blackmail?

574
00:49:30,634 --> 00:49:35,339
She's a public defender.
She doesn't get paid!

575
00:49:35,973 --> 00:49:37,174
Let me go!

576
00:49:37,541 --> 00:49:40,043
-Gosh!
-Oh my goodness.

577
00:49:44,815 --> 00:49:49,152
What if I hadn't turned up?
You should have come with someone.

578
00:49:49,219 --> 00:49:50,620
I will next time.

579
00:49:50,921 --> 00:49:54,524
If I were a little late,
you could have gotten hurt.

580
00:49:54,591 --> 00:49:55,926
I'm not hurt.

581
00:49:56,193 --> 00:49:58,862
Think about it. If I weren't there...

582
00:49:59,162 --> 00:50:02,199
Is it so hard to say "thank you"?

583
00:50:02,399 --> 00:50:03,767
But I'm not thankful.

584
00:50:03,834 --> 00:50:06,737
Why not? I saved you.

585
00:50:06,803 --> 00:50:08,305
You're a judge.

586
00:50:08,805 --> 00:50:12,809
Taking my side could give
the wrong impression.

587
00:50:12,876 --> 00:50:17,114
I think you forgot about
how fair you should be as a judge.

588
00:50:19,750 --> 00:50:21,685
She's an oddity in this legal world.

589
00:50:21,752 --> 00:50:24,121
How did she become a lawyer
with such a temper?

590
00:50:30,093 --> 00:50:32,429
-I didn't say anything.
-Walk forward.

591
00:50:33,196 --> 00:50:35,198
-What?
-Hurry!

592
00:50:35,365 --> 00:50:36,400
Why?

593
00:50:56,253 --> 00:50:57,854
I should get going.

594
00:50:58,955 --> 00:51:00,690
Are you thankful now?

595
00:51:00,757 --> 00:51:03,393
No, you were going this way anyway.

596
00:51:04,127 --> 00:51:05,896
Your skirt is turned around.

597
00:51:12,169 --> 00:51:15,705
She is such an odd one. What an oddity.

598
00:51:17,074 --> 00:51:18,341
REASONS FOR APPEAL

599
00:51:22,479 --> 00:51:24,448
MIN'S FARM

600
00:51:34,157 --> 00:51:35,392
Isn't that strange?

601
00:51:35,459 --> 00:51:37,561
How can a total stranger report him?

602
00:51:37,627 --> 00:51:40,730
And from Gapyeong,
which is far from Ganghwa Island.

603
00:51:53,143 --> 00:51:55,178
MIN'S FARM

604
00:51:59,883 --> 00:52:03,887
Hello! What can I get you?
Today's peaches are great.

605
00:52:04,321 --> 00:52:05,722
Are you Mun Sung-nam?

606
00:52:06,623 --> 00:52:08,225
You reported Park Su-ha to the police.

607
00:52:08,291 --> 00:52:11,862
What is it now?
Did you come to take away my reward?

608
00:52:11,928 --> 00:52:14,931
Go away. I'm not selling fruit to you.

609
00:52:15,232 --> 00:52:19,970
I could take your reward,
if you don't tell me the truth.

610
00:52:20,270 --> 00:52:22,272
Why are you doing this?

611
00:52:22,339 --> 00:52:26,443
It's not as if I broke the law
by reporting a bad person.

612
00:52:26,510 --> 00:52:27,878
Of course not.

613
00:52:28,044 --> 00:52:32,382
But how could you report Park Su-ha
when you don't know him?

614
00:52:32,449 --> 00:52:37,354
Someone told me I could make money
by reporting him.

615
00:52:37,420 --> 00:52:39,289
That's why I did it.

616
00:52:39,356 --> 00:52:40,991
Who was that?

617
00:52:41,057 --> 00:52:43,560
It was someone who bought some fruit.

618
00:52:43,627 --> 00:52:46,963
He told me when I gave him a discount.

619
00:52:47,030 --> 00:52:49,132
Do you remember his face?

620
00:52:49,199 --> 00:52:50,700
Could you remember if you saw a photo?

621
00:52:51,735 --> 00:52:53,570
If I see a photo I guess.

622
00:52:56,973 --> 00:53:01,178
Is he among these men?

623
00:53:05,949 --> 00:53:07,484
No, he's not here.

624
00:53:08,084 --> 00:53:10,921
-You're not lying, are you?
-No.

625
00:53:10,987 --> 00:53:15,358
Shall I just choose one of them?
Will you let me keep my reward then?

626
00:53:16,826 --> 00:53:17,894
I'm done here.

627
00:54:10,113 --> 00:54:13,250
Please don't avoid me and talk to me.

628
00:54:13,717 --> 00:54:16,319
Okay. Let's talk.

629
00:54:35,705 --> 00:54:38,074
Talk to me. What do you want to say?

630
00:54:39,676 --> 00:54:44,481
There's so much to say.
I haven't been able to thank you.

631
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:47,984
Thank you so much
for believing and defending me.

632
00:54:49,119 --> 00:54:53,390
Okay. I accept your gratitude.
Okay? What else?

633
00:54:54,057 --> 00:54:56,059
Why can't I contact you?

634
00:54:56,760 --> 00:54:58,161
I'm really busy.

635
00:54:58,228 --> 00:55:01,531
To handle 30 cases a month,
I need more than 30 hours a day.

636
00:55:01,598 --> 00:55:05,101
So I have no time for you. And?

637
00:55:06,036 --> 00:55:08,338
Did I really not like you?

638
00:55:09,706 --> 00:55:12,776
You didn't like me. You didn't respect me.

639
00:55:12,842 --> 00:55:16,680
You were rude and nagged me.
Is there anything else?

640
00:55:17,647 --> 00:55:19,115
What about you?

641
00:55:19,983 --> 00:55:21,785
Did you not like me?

642
00:55:26,156 --> 00:55:27,657
Shall I be honest?

643
00:55:27,957 --> 00:55:31,494
I didn't just dislike you,
I was so tired of you.

644
00:55:31,761 --> 00:55:35,432
Do you know how ridiculous it was
to see you pretend to be an adult?

645
00:55:35,498 --> 00:55:38,868
That's not all.
You were good at making me mad.

646
00:55:39,269 --> 00:55:43,840
Why did you defend me then?
You said you didn't like me.

647
00:55:45,608 --> 00:55:47,610
I guess that's why you got the wrong idea.

648
00:55:48,078 --> 00:55:49,579
Didn't I tell you?

649
00:55:49,646 --> 00:55:53,249
You're not special to me. Min Jun-guk is.

650
00:55:53,316 --> 00:55:58,121
I had to get an acquittal
to keep believing in the law.

651
00:55:58,188 --> 00:56:00,023
That's why I defended you so hard.

652
00:56:03,093 --> 00:56:07,397
I got all I wanted out of this trial.
I also learned what a lawyer is.

653
00:56:07,464 --> 00:56:11,401
I'm grateful for that.
But that's as far as it goes.

654
00:56:11,735 --> 00:56:14,371
So you should stop, too. Okay?

655
00:56:15,605 --> 00:56:17,107
It's late. I should go.

656
00:56:20,043 --> 00:56:23,213
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

657
00:56:24,080 --> 00:56:27,450
Even though you hate me so much,

658
00:56:28,084 --> 00:56:29,853
couldn't you stay?

659
00:56:32,422 --> 00:56:33,456
Let me go.

660
00:56:34,290 --> 00:56:37,327
I feel like all my connections
to this world have been cut off.

661
00:56:37,627 --> 00:56:40,530
If you let me go, then...

662
00:56:46,870 --> 00:56:47,937
Mr. Cha.

663
00:56:54,477 --> 00:56:59,482
You're stuck in a situation, right?
Say you're going to watch a movie with me.

664
00:57:01,084 --> 00:57:04,454
That's right.
We were supposed to watch a movie.

665
00:57:06,122 --> 00:57:10,226
I have to go.
I'm sorry. I'm too late, right?

666
00:57:23,606 --> 00:57:28,011
Don't go!

667
00:57:48,164 --> 00:57:50,500
Don't go!

668
00:57:52,869 --> 00:57:54,170
Please.

669
00:58:07,884 --> 00:58:10,286
-Thank you.
-For what?

670
00:58:10,887 --> 00:58:12,956
Please go to Soojik-dong.

671
00:58:13,122 --> 00:58:16,759
No, let me off at the corner.
I can take a bus.

672
00:58:16,826 --> 00:58:18,928
Don't get off. I'll take you home.

673
00:58:44,921 --> 00:58:46,523
I guess this happened before.

674
00:59:02,071 --> 00:59:04,073
-Go on in.
-Okay.

675
00:59:04,974 --> 00:59:06,209
Thanks for today.

676
00:59:07,744 --> 00:59:09,445
Then buy me lunch tomorrow.

677
00:59:09,512 --> 00:59:11,548
Then I take back my thanks.

678
00:59:12,048 --> 00:59:17,387
You haven't changed.
I don't have to worry. I should go.

679
01:00:18,381 --> 01:00:19,849
Why isn't the bus coming?

680
01:00:42,572 --> 01:00:46,142
Do you still resent me?

681
01:00:49,312 --> 01:00:50,480
No.

682
01:00:52,081 --> 01:00:53,783
I don't resent you anymore.

683
01:00:53,950 --> 01:00:59,055
Then can I ask you
why I can't be your boyfriend?

684
01:01:22,445 --> 01:01:24,781
I know this doesn't make sense.

685
01:01:26,716 --> 01:01:28,818
I can't believe it either.

686
01:01:41,898 --> 01:01:44,167
But I keep thinking about him.

687
01:01:54,577 --> 01:01:56,646
I can't believe this.

688
01:02:00,149 --> 01:02:01,784
I know this doesn't make sense.

689
01:02:03,219 --> 01:02:05,455
I think I like him.

690
01:02:11,027 --> 01:02:13,029
What should I do with you?

691
01:02:17,300 --> 01:02:20,837
So I'm going to end it. I have to end it.

